y-svet/ceska-republika-bude-plnit-zavazky-plynouci-z-clenstvi-v-nato_200109132204_mkopp|title= \u010cesk\u00e1 republika bude plnit z\u00e1vazky plynouc\u00ed z \u010dlenstv\u00ed v NATO|language=cz|website=irozhlas.cz}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Cyprus}}\n| <ref name=hri.org>{{cite web |author1=ANA |title=Friday declared day of mourning in Greece |url=http://www.hri.org/news/greek/ana/2001/01-09-14.ana.html |publisher=Athens News Agency |date=September 14, 2001}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Greece}}\n| <ref name=hri.org/>\n|-\n| {{flag|Israel}}\n| <ref>{{cite web |title=Israel Reacts to Terrorist Attacks on the US |url=https://mfa.gov.il/MFA/MFA-Archive/2001/Pages/Israel%20Reacts%20to%20Terrorist%20Attacks%20on%20the%20US%20-%2011-.aspx |website=mfa.gov.il |publisher=Israel Ministry of Foreign Affairs |date=September 11, 2001}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Poland}}\n| 3\n| Several Polish citizens were among those killed.<ref name=PolandMourning/>\n|-\n| {{flag|Russia}}\n| 2002\n| 1\n| Victims of the [[2002 Khankala Mi-26 crash]]\n| <ref>{{cite web |author1=President of Russia |title=President Vladimir Putin signed a decree declaring a day of mourning for the helicopter crash in the Chechen Republic |url=http://en.kremlin.ru/events/president/news/27316 |website=en.kremlin.ru |date=August 20, 2002}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Russia}}\n| 2002\n| 1\n| Victims of the [[Moscow theater hostage crisis]]\n| <ref>{{cite web |title=\u0423\u043a\u0430\u0437 \u041f\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u043e\u0442 27.10.2002 \u0433. \u2116 1263 |url=http://kremlin.ru/acts/bank/18780 |website=\u041f\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 |language=ru}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Poland}}\n| rowspan=2| 2004\n| 2\n| rowspan=2| Victims of the [[2004 Madrid train bombings]]\n| 4 Polish citizens were among those killed.<ref name=PolandMourning