y Product\n|Always Being Clean ([[Simplified Chinese characters|simplified chinese]]: ABC\u4e2a\u4eba\u62a4\u7406)\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Chinese girl groups]]\n[[Category:Mandopop musical groups]]\n[[Category:Chinese pop music groups]]\n[[Category:Chinese dance music groups]]\n[[Category:Mandarin-language singers]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2015]]\n[[Category:2015 establishments in China]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Super Impassioned Net Generation (SING)\n| background       = group_or_band\n| image            = SING_3rd_Anniversary.jpg\n| image_size       = 350\n| landscape        = yes\n| alt              = SING 3rd Anniversary on Aug 27, 2018\n| caption          = SING 3rd Anniversary on Aug 27, 2018\n| alias            = SING Girls\n| origin           = [[China]]\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[C-pop]]|[[Mandopop]]|[[Dance music]]|[[Electro House]]}}\n| years_active     = 2015\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|[[KuGou]]|Qigu Culture|JSJ International Entertainment}}\n| associated_acts  = [[Rocket Girls (band)|Rocket Girls]]\n| website          = {{url|http://sing.fanxing.kugou.com/}}\n| current_members  = * Qin Yu (Sophie)\n* Bian Li (Jessica)\n* Lin Hui (Haha)\n* [[Lai Meiyun]] (Sunny)\n* Jiang Shen (Debbie)\n* Xu Shiyin (Valentina)\n* Chen Li (Pink)\n* Wu Yao (Miko)\n| former_members   = * Lin Jinyi (Magical)\n* Cai Sha (SaSa)\n* Wang Wenjie (Candy)\n* Chen Wenrou (Ruby)\n* Gong Tianying (Lorinda)|\n}}\n\n'''SING''', also known as '''Super Impassioned Net Generation''' ({{zh|s=SING\u5973\u56e2|t=SING\u5973\u5718|p=/s\u026a\u014b/ n\u01da tu\u00e1n|l=Sing Girls' Group}}) is a Chinese [[girl group]] formed by [[KuGou|KuGou Music]] in 2015 with 10 members, selected from different regions of [[China]]. The current line-up is composed of eight members, and they primarily produce [[electronic dance music]] inspired by traditional Chinese music.\n\n==History==\n===2015: Formation and debut===\nSING debuted in 2015 with ten members on August 10, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.qq.com/a/20150811/037962.htm|title=S.I.N.G Debut (S.I.N.G\u5973\u5b50\u5076\u50cf\u56e2\u4f53\u51fa\u9053 \u6d3b\u529b\u7efd\u653e\u9752\u6625\u544a\u767d)|work=[[Tencent]] News|date=August 11, 2015|language=Chinese}}</ref> Given the limitations on budget, the group did not rely on income from concert tickets, instead gaining primary revenues from royalty, licensing fees, and selling merchandise.<ref name=\"sina_news\">{{cite web|url=http://k.sina.com.cn/article_6283799853_1768b2d2d001007dp1.html|title=Trying to survive as an idol group (101\u5973\u56e2\u56fe\u9274\u2460\uff1a\u7535\u5b50\u56fd\u98ce\u5973\u56e2\u6c42\u751f\u8bb0)|work=[[Sina Corp|Sina News]]|date=June 3, 2018|language=Chinese}}</ref>\n\n===2016: Line-up changes===\nFour members suspended their activities in 2016, and three new members were added to the group.<ref name=\"sina_news\" />\n\n===2017: Change in sound and breakthrough===\nIn September, SING released the single \"Moonlight Thoughts\" ({{zh|s=\u5bc4\u660e\u6708|p=J\u00ec m\u00edngyu\u00e8}}), their first ever Chinese-style electronic dance song. The single helped the group gain popularity and momentum in China.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://music.yule.sohu.com/20170928/n514911808.shtml|title=The Chinese style EDM (SING\u5973\u56e2\u300a\u5bc4\u660e\u6708\u300b\u53d1\u5e03 \u534e\u8bed\"\u7535\u5b50\u56fd\u98ce\"\u7b2c\u4e00\u67aa)|work=[[Sohu]]|date=September 28, 2017|language=Chinese}}</ref> In December, the group held a [[Christmas]] live concert named ''Part of Me''. Following the concert, Lin Jinyi suspended her activities due to health concerns.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.ifeng.com/a/20171226/43016520_0.shtml|title=Chinese EDM Group SING live concert (\u7535\u5b50\u56fd\u98ce\u5973\u56e2SING\u5973\u56e2\u516c\u6f14 \u5f15\u7c89\u4e1d\u72c2\u6253CALL)|work=[[Phoenix Television]]|date=December 26, 2018|language=Chinese}}</ref>\n\nIn November, the group released their first international album ''SING'' on [[iTunes]] and [[Spotify]].\n\n===2018-2019: Continued success===\n\nThree members of SING participated in the reality idol competition [[Produce 101 (Chinese TV series)|''Produce 101'']] in March 2018. Jiang Shen and Xu Shiyin finished at 23rd and 75th place, respectively; [[Lai Meiyun]] made the final line up at 6th place and successfully debuted as a member of [[Rocket Girls (band)|Rocket Girls]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/1108147.shtml|title=Chinese idol competition reality show 'Produce 101' reveals members of China's newest girl band Rocket Girls|work=[[Global Times]]|date=June 24, 2018}}</ref>\n\nSING performed on the 2nd International Youth Conference in [[Shenzhen]] on August 12.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://passport.weibo.com/visitor/visitor?entry=miniblog&a=enter&url=https%3A%2F%2Fweibo.com%2F5281360151%2FGuliFwPfm&domain=.weibo.com&ua=php-sso_sdk_client-0.6.28&_rand=1550245267.1133|title=The 2nd International Youth Conference|website=passport.weibo.com}}</ref> Sophie presented a speech titled \"[https://www.bilibili.com/video/av29380820 Integration of Youth Culture and Traditional Culture from the Perspective of Electronic Chinese Style Music]\" to introduce insights on young people\u2019s inheritance and innovation in traditional Chinese culture based on her personal experience.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bilibili.com/read/cv957801/|title=Integration of Youth Culture and Traditional Culture from the Perspective of Electronic Chinese Style Music|last=SING\u5973\u56e2|website=www.bilibili.com}}</ref>\n\nSING joined the TV Show competition \"''Wo Yao Shang Chun Wan''\" ([[simplified chinese]]: \u6211\u8981\u4e0a\u6625\u665a)  with \"Moonlight Thoughts\" on December 29, 2018. This TV show competition selected the performance for the CCTV Spring Festival Event. SING lost but advanced to the final through fan voting. ([https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IjAkmXWK8U0&t=34s youtube] )<ref>{{Citation|last=CCTV\u6625\u665a|title=[2018\u6211\u8981\u4e0a\u6625\u665a] \u56fd\u98ce\u7f8e\u5c11\u5973\uff01\u7535\u97f3\u5973\u56e2SING\u300a\u5bc4\u660e\u6708\u300b\u5f15\u53d1\u5168\u7403\u6a21\u4eff \u98de\u82b1\u4ee4\u4e5f\u96be\u4e0d\u5012 \u8fd9\u662f\u4e2a\u6709\u6587\u5316\u7684\u56e2\uff01 {{!}} CCTV\u6625\u665a|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IjAkmXWK8U0&t=34s|access-date=2019-02-08}}</ref>\n\nXu Shiyin released her first solo \"Bai Yi Shao Nian\" ([[Simplified chinese|Simplified Chinese]]: \u767d\u8863\u5c11\u5e74) on March 14 and its accompanying music video on June 26.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ent.tom.com/201807/1907256781.html|title=SING\u5973\u56e2\u8bb8\u8bd7\u8335\u539f\u521b\u66f2\u300a\u767d\u8863\u5c11\u5e74\u300bPV\u4e0a\u7ebf_TOM\u5a31\u4e50|website=ent.tom.com}}</ref> The song was used as the ending theme for the drama \"I Will Never Let You Go\" ([[simplified chinese]]: \u5c0f\u5973\u82b1\u4e0d\u5f03) which aired on January 8, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://culture.people.com.cn/n1/2019/0108/c1013-30510106.html|title=SING\u5973\u56e2\u8bb8\u8bd7\u8335\u732e\u5531\u300a\u5c0f\u5973\u82b1\u4e0d\u5f03\u300b\u5531\u4f5c\u53cc\u7edd--\u6587\u5316--\u4eba\u6c11\u7f51|website=culture.people.com.cn}}</ref>\n\nThe variety show ''SING HOME'' began airing in 2019, with each episode having a different theme and featuring content such as playing games, team discussions, and interacting with fans. \n\nDebbie released her first solo song \"Mermaid\" on January 4, and its music video on January 21. Debbie explained that she chose the title because she hoped her first solo would attract people to her, like the singing of a mermaid.\n\nSING performed the song \"Ru Meng Ling\" ([[simplified chinese]]: \u5982\u68a6\u4ee4) in the final of \"''Wo Yao Shang Chun Wan''\" ([[simplified chinese]]: \u6211\u8981\u4e0a\u6625\u665a) in January 26. They lost the judges vote 0-5 to their competitor. ([https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UuVQA41DOtw youtube]) SING, [[Han Xue (actress)|Han Xue]], and [[Wu Mochou]] performed the song \"''Hui Jia Guo Nian La''\"([[simplified chinese]]: \u56de\u5bb6\u8fc7\u5e74\u5566) on the CCTV Internet Spring Festival Event in January 28.([https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yIsXldBz7Mg youtube]) SING, [[Han Xue (actress)|Han Xue]], and Oscar Qian performed the song \"''Nian Ye Fan''\" ([[simplified chinese]]: \u5e74\u591c\u996d)  for the Hunan TV Spring Festival Event on January 29.([https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ppxNwlxGr4w youtube])\nSING performed the song \"Huan Le Zhong Guo Nian\" ([[simplified chinese]]: \u6b22\u4e50\u4e2d\u56fd\u5e74)  for the Jiangxi TV Spring Festival Event on February 3.([https://m.weibo.cn/status/4335699329270759 Weibo]) SING performed the song \"Tuan Tuan Yuan Yuan\" ([[simplified chinese]]: \u56e2\u56e2\u5706\u5706) for the CCTV Spring Festival Event Countdown on February 4.([https://www.bilibili.com/video/av42648777?share_medium=android&share_source=copy_link&bbid=XY329E639E3297D3625EBC6A30098B602C166&ts=1549306819956 bilibili]) SING performed the song \"Ru Meng Ling\" ([[simplified chinese]]: \u5982\u68a6\u4ee4)  and \"Qian Nian\" ([[simplified chinese]]: \u5343\u5e74) for the GuangDong TV Spring Festival on February 4.([https://www.bilibili.com/video/av43408217 bilibili]) Their song \"Tuan Tuan Yuan Yuan\" ([[simplified Chinese]]: \u56e2\u56e2\u5706\u5706) was used as the background music of \"The Reunion\" on the 7th Hong Kong Lunar New Year Firework Show on February 6.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hk01.com/\u89aa\u5b50/290200/\u8cc0\u6b72\u7159\u82b1-\u521d\u4e8c\u7159\u82b1\u532f\u6f14\u6709\u8c6c\u9f3b\u5716\u6848-\u56db\u500b\u7747\u7159\u82b1\u975a\u4f4d\u63a8\u4ecb|title=\u3010\u8cc0\u6b72\u7159\u82b1\u3011\u521d\u4e8c\u7159\u82b1\u532f\u6f14\u6709\u8c6c\u9f3b\u5716\u6848 \u56db\u500b\u7747\u7159\u82b1\u975a\u4f4d\u63a8\u4ecb|website=\u9999\u6e2f01|language=zh-HK}}</ref>\n\nXu Shiyin released her second solo \"You Are Not Wrong\" ([[Simplified Chinese characters|simplified chinese]] : \u662f\u4f60\u6ca1\u9519\u4e86) in March 14. The song was written by Shiyin and composed by Mikey Jiao. It represented the discovery of her career and thanked the people who supported her.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ent.people.com.cn/n1/2019/0315/c1012-30978468.html|title=\u8bb8\u8bd7\u8335\u53d1\u5e03\u6700\u65b0\u72ec\u7acb\u4f5c\u8bcd\u5355\u66f2\u300a\u662f\u4f60\u6ca1\u9519\u4e86\u300b\u00a0--\u4eba\u6c11\u7f51\u5a31\u4e50\u9891\u9053--\u4eba\u6c11\u7f51|website=ent.people.com.cn}}</ref>  She also released her third song \"Yi Sheng Tian Ya\"([[simplified chinese]]: \u4e00\u751f\u5929\u6daf) on 12 November. \n\nDebbie was invited to participate in the Asian Cultural Carnival on May 15. She performed the song \"A Youthful Asia\" with [[William Chan]], [[Lay Zhang|Zhang Yixing]], and Young Asia Group. SING performed the songs \"Ru Meng Ling\" ([[simplified chinese]]: \u5982\u68a6\u4ee4) and \"Bu Xian\" ([[simplified chinese]]: \u4e0d\u7fa1) on Yo!Bang on May 26.\n\nBian Li released her first solo \"Someday\" ([[Pinyin]]: Mou Yi Tian)([[simplified chinese]]: \u67d0\u4e00\u5929) on July 5. Later, on November 4, she released her second song \"Deng\" ([[simplified chinese]]: \u7b49).\n\nOn March 17, SING performed at the One Yeah Pop Up+ Festival held in [[Xi'an]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sohu.com/a/300872156_729517|title=2019\u73a9\u91ce\u6f6e\u9752\u5e74\u6587\u5316\u8282\uff08\u897f\u5b89\u7ad9\uff09\u76db\u5927\u97f3\u4e50\u8282\u9080\u4f60\u6765\uff01_\u8bf4\u5531|website=www.sohu.com}}</ref> SING then performed the songs \"Guo Chao Shi Dai\" ([[Simplified Chinese characters|Simplified chinese]]: \u56fd\u6f6e\u65f6\u4ee3) and \"Chuan Ren\" ([[simplified chinese]]: \u4f20\u4eba) in another edition of the same festival on May 11.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chinanews.com/cul/2019/05-11/8833660.shtml|title=\"\u6709\u95f4\u56fd\u6f6e\u9986\"\u8bb2\u8ff0\u4e2d\u56fd\u98ce \u4e3b\u9898\u66f2\u7531SING\u5973\u56e2\u6f14\u5531-\u4e2d\u65b0\u7f51|website=www.chinanews.com}}</ref> \n\nOn August 8, SING released their Chinese Style Electronic Music digital album ''Jie Meng''. The album includes three songs, which are \"Jie Meng\", \"Shao Nian Zhong Guo\" and \"Pi Pa Xing\". SING celebrated their 4th anniversary since debut and also released the song \"Hua Qiang\" ([[Simplified Chinese]]: \u82b1\u67aa) on October 25 in Beijing, China. On November 17, SING was announced as the winner of the Rising Popularity Group of the Year award and also performed the song \"Hua Qiang\" ([[Simplified Chinese]]: \u82b1\u67aa) at the Asia Music Festival 2019 in Shenzhen, China.\n\n==Members==\n===Current===\n*Qin Yu (\u79e6\u745c) (Sophie)\n*Bian Li (\u8fb9\u4e3d) (Jessica)\n*Lin Hui (\u6797\u6167) (Haha)\n*Jiang Shen (\u848b\u7533) (Debbie)\n*Xu Shiyin (\u8bb8\u8bd7\u8335) (Valentina)\n*Chen Li (\u9648\u4e3d) (Pink)\n*Wu Yao (\u5434\u7476) (Miko)\n*[[Lai Meiyun]] (\u8d56\u7f8e\u4e91) (Sunny) (currently active in [[Rocket Girls 101]])\n\n===Former===\n*Lin Jinyi (\u6797\u6d25\u4f0a) (Magical)\n*Cai Sha (\u8521\u838e) (SaSa)\n*Wang Wenjie (\u738b\u6587\u6d01) (Candy)\n*Chen Wenrou (\u9648\u6e29\u67d4) (Ruby)\n*Gong Tianying (\u9f9a\u5929\u9896) (Lorinda)\n\n==Discography==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" | Album details\n|-\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''SING'' (SING\u540c\u540d\u4e13\u8f91)\n|\n*Released: December 29, 2017\n*Label: JSJ International Entertainment\n*Formats: [[Compact disc|CD]], [[Music download|digital download]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Jie Meng'' (\u89e3\u68a6)\n|\n*Released: August 10, 2019\n*Formats: digital download\n|-\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"1\" | Peak chart