ranakhoond|Imran Akhoond }}\n* [http://images.dawn.com/news/1176349/the-making-of-coke-studio-a-deepika-wannabe-the-atari-on-set-and-other-fun-facts Dawn News]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Akhoond, Imran Muhammad}}\n[[Category:Pakistani guitarists]]\n[[Category:Pakistani pop singers]]\n[[Category:Pakistani male singers]]\n[[Category:Pakistani Sunni Muslims]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Karachi]]\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century guitarists]]\n[[Category:21st-century male musicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=December 2014}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2014}}\n{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name                = Imran Akhoond\n| alias               = Imran Muhammad Akhoond\n| image               =\n| image_size          = 250px\n| Img_capt            = Imran Akhoond in Coke Studio (Session 7)\n| native_name         =\n| birth_date      = \n| birth_place         = [[Karachi]], [[Sindh, Pakistan|Sindh Province]] of [[Pakistan]]\n| background          = solo_singer\n| birth_name          = {{Nastaliq|\u0639\u0645\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0627\u062e\u0648\u0646\u062f}}\n| death_date          =\n| instrument          = Vocals, [[Acoustic guitar|guitar]]\n| genre               = Bluse rock (1990\u2013present)\n| Occupation          = Musician, guitarist\n| Years_active        = 1990\u2013present\n| label               = \n| associated_acts     = [[Shehzad Roy]], [[Awaz]], [[Strings (band)]]\n| website             = \n}}\n\n'''Imran Muhammad Akhoond''' is a [[Pakistani people|Pakistani]] guitarist, music composer songwriter. He is far famed as a Lead Guitarist for renowned Pakistani Pop Singer, Philanthropist and humanitarian,UNODC National Goodwill Ambassador Shehzad Roy.<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/media/rm2647579648/nm4119037?ref_=nmmd_md_pv Shehzad Roy and Imran Akhoond in Concert]</ref> His incessant attitude towards exploring different Genres 